This product is a C# port of and derivative work of Philter, the rule-based
PHI de-identification pipeline developed by the UCSF Bakar Computational
Health Sciences Institute (BCHSI):

    Philter (philter-ucsf)
    https://github.com/BCHSI/philter-ucsf
    BSD 3-Clause License
    Copyright (c) 2018, Regents of the University of California
    Citation: Norgeot, B., Muenzen, K., Peterson, T.A. et al. "Protected Health
    Information filter (Philter): accurately and securely de-identifying
    free-text clinical notes." npj Digital Medicine 3, 57 (2020).

The C# port was made via philter-lite (https://github.com/TimOrme/philter-lite),
a production-oriented fork of philter-ucsf against which Philter.NET is
cross-benchmarked for fidelity. The base filter pipeline configuration
(`philter_delta.json`) and the lookup sets in `Configuration/sets/` are the
philter-ucsf artifacts verbatim (the 313 filters and the
firstnames/lastnames/nonames gazetteers). The upstream BSD-3 attribution and
the Regents of the University of California copyright apply to those artifacts;
modifications and additions ship under this project's BSD-3 license alongside.

The C# filter engine implementation, configuration loader, sidecar
mechanism, and POS tagger integrations are original work.

---

The Philter.NET.PerceptronTagger package embeds and ports the NLTK averaged
perceptron part-of-speech tagger:

    Averaged Perceptron Tagger
    Copyright 2013 Matthew Honnibal
    NLTK port / modifications Copyright 2015 The NLTK Project
    MIT License

    The C# inference port (AveragedPerceptron.cs, PerceptronPosTagger.cs) is
    derived from nltk/tag/perceptron.py. The embedded model data
    (averaged_perceptron_tagger_eng.{weights,tagdict,classes}.json) is the
    pretrained English model distributed by the NLTK Data project under the
    MIT License (per the NLTK data index). Permission notice retained per MIT.

